    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Offered is a driver-focused 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the legendary S54 3.2L inline-six power plant. This high-revving unit utilizes individual throttle bodies and dual-VANOS variable valve timing to deliver linear power up to an 8,000 RPM redline. The drivetrain is anchored by a Getrag 6-speed manual transmission and a factory M-Variable limited-slip differential, ensuring mechanical purity. Critical preventative maintenance has been addressed, including documented rod bearing replacement and rear subframe reinforcement to mitigate floor-pan fatigue. The chassis remains composed with refreshed bushings and factory-spec dampening, retaining the platform's signature communicative steering rack and balanced weight distribution. While exhibiting minor aesthetic wear commensurate with its mileage, the mechanical vitals and compression across all six cylinders remain within enthusiast-grade tolerances.",
